<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
'''Murder 4''' is a cross-compatible player-versus-player horror [[Special:MyLanguage/:Category:Game worlds|game world]], created by ''Jar'' in 2020. Up to twenty-four players can play at a time, but a minimum of three players must be present to begin. There are three possible roles to play as: The '''Detective''', '''Bystander(s)''', and '''Murderer'''. There are clues, photographs, weapons, and hazards that players will encounter. The objective of the Murderer is to eliminate every player in the mansion. The objective of the Detective is to find out and eliminate the murderer, and the Bystanders is to work together to identify and neutralize the Murderer.
</div>

<span id="Game_modifiers"></span>
==Modyfikatory gry==

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The instance master can optionally use Game Modifiers to change the rules.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* '''Teams Enabled''' - summons twelve circles to stand on in the lobby. More than one player can inhabit the same circle, guaranteeing to pair them with the same role as everyone in the circle, allowing there to be more than one Detective or Murderer.
* '''Scrambled Spawns''' - randomly selecting a room for players to start in the mansion, except the Detective always spawns in the Study.
* '''One Unlock Only''' - spawns one unlockable weapon for the first player to collect all five clues, and no more clues will spawn for anyone else.
* '''Invisible Knives''' is a game modifier that only allows the Murderer to see knives that are on the ground. Knives are still visible in the Murderer's hands.
</div>

